    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've researched and documented:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n**6 files to touch:**\n\n### 1. NEW: `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nSelf-contained INI parser and stringifier following the `TOMLObject.zig`/`JSON5Object.zig` pattern:\n- `create()` — builds the namespace object with `parse` and `stringify`\n- `parse()` — processes input line-by-line: skips blank lines/`;`/`#` comments, handles `[section]` headers as nested JS objects, splits `key = value` on `=` with whitespace trimming, throws descriptively on invalid lines\n- `stringify()` — iterates JS object properties via `jsc.JSPropertyIterator`; nested objects → `[section]` headers; primitives → `key = value`; uses `wtf.StringBuilder` for output\n\n### 2. `src/bun.js/api.zig` (line ~34)\nAdd: `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n\n### 3. `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` (4 sub-changes)\n- Struct field (~line 70): `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);`\n- Export (~line 140): `@export(&BunObject.INI, ...)`\n- Getter fn (~line 1289): `pub fn getINIObject(...) { return INIObject.create(globalThis); }`\n- Import (~line 2083): `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;`\n\n### 4. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`\nAdd `macro(INI)` alphabetically between `Glob` and `JSON5`\n\n### 5. `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`\nAdd `INI BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to the `bunObjectTable` hash, after `JSON5`\n\n### 6. `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`\nAdd `namespace INI { parse(input: string): Record<string, any>; stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string; }` with JSDoc examples, after the `JSONC` namespace block",
